data.text: Republic of the Philippines PROFESSIONAL REGULATION COMMISSION Manila TEACHER LICENSURE EXAMINATION RESULTS RELEASED IN FORTY-FOUR (44) WORKING DAYS The Professional Regulation Commission (PRC) announces that 27,060 elementary teachers out of 76,626 examinees and 23,772 secondary teachers out of 65,106 examinees successfully passed the Licensure Examination for Teachers (L.E.T.) given by the Board for Professional Teachers on August 25, 2002 in 18 different testing centers all over the Philippines. The Board for Professional Teachers is composed of former Chairperson, Dr. Avelina T. Llagas; Dr. Gloria G. Salandanan, Chairperson; Dr. Martha A. Mogol, Vice- Chairperson; Dr. Brenda B. Corpuz and Mr. Arnulfo H. Empleo, members. The results of examination with respect to twenty-eight (28) examinees were withheld pending final determination of their liabilities under the rules and regulations governing licensure examinations. Registration for the issuance of Certificates of Registration and Professional Identification Cards will be scheduled after the oathtaking. The requirements for the issuance of Certificate of Registration and Professional Identification Card are the following: duly accomplished Oath Form or Panunumpa ng Propesyonal, latest Community Tax Certificate (Cedula); one (1) piece passport size picture, one (1) piece 2 x 2 picture with nametag; metered documentary stamps for the Oath Form and Certificate of Registration, and 1 short brown envelope with name and profession; and to pay the following fees: Initial Registration Fee of P400; and P300 for Professional Identification Card. Successful examinees should personally register and sign in the Roster of Registered Professionals. The schedules for the oathtaking ceremonies are as follows: REGION DATE NATIONAL CAPITAL REGION (N.C.R.) Sunday, November 3, 2002 REGION IV Sunday, November 3, 2002 LUCENA Monday, November 4, 2002 PAMPANGA Saturday, November 9, 2002 GENERAL SANTOS Saturday, November 9, 2002 ZAMBOANGA Sunday, November 10, 2002 DAVAO Sunday, November 10, 2002 LEGAZPI Monday, November 11, 2002 TACLOBAN Friday, November 15, 2002 ILOILO Saturday, November 16, 2002 CEBU Saturday, November 16, 2002
